<definition id="fs-id1914007"><term>basal metabolic rate (BMR)</term> <meaning id="fs-id1932509"> amount of energy expended by the body at rest</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1438518"><term>conduction</term> <meaning id="fs-id1924000">transfer of heat through physical contact</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id3078617"><term>convection</term> <meaning id="fs-id2152956">transfer of heat between the skin and air or water</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2461503"><term>evaporation</term> <meaning id="fs-id2538062">transfer of heat that occurs when water changes from a liquid to a gas</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1571300"><term>metabolic rate</term> <meaning id="fs-id1539766">amount of energy consumed minus the amount of energy expended by the body</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id2271133"><term>radiation</term> <meaning id="fs-id2705727">transfer of heat via infrared waves</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1479444"><term>thermoneutral</term> <meaning id="fs-id1590191">external temperature at which the body does not expend any energy for thermoregulation, about 84 °F</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1874417"><term>thermoregulation</term> <meaning id="fs-id1369842">process of regulating the temperature of the body</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
